I had ordered a small vanilla iced coffee and received a black coffee with ice and hazelnut. I had told them directly that they had made it wrong. They had gotten an attitude with me, and after asking to speak with a manager I was turned down and ignored. They were very unprofessional. I do understand there is no anaphylaxis related to hazelnut syrup but there is irritation related to this and I am allergic to nuts, so the irritation has made my day of touring very uncomfortable. I have also now seen the amount of complaints due to the attitude and this does need to be fixed. They should also be given proper training in not only making the coffee but food health standards as I watched a worker wipe her nose barehanded while proceeding to make more coffee.

All staff here are extremely rude to customers. They make your drink wrong and they get an attitude with you! I'm sorry but at over at over $5 a pop, I want my drink made as instructed on my mobile order ticket, not how they feel like making it and hold the attitude, PLEASE! This store needs additional training big time and if that doesn't work, then can the whole crew and start over. You need good managers that don't allow this kind of behavior towards customers. If you don't like being in customer service because you have a bad attitude then please do us all a favor and go find another job!
